&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>In the Sanskrit language, the word Kriya means that which happens. Karma means which is done.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Whatever needs to be done for that you need to have your desire and intention. In Sanskrit it is called Sankalp. So without Sankalp, you cannot do any karma.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>